<planning_requirements>
The plan must cover:

**Backend phases first**:
1. Query services:
   - ReportDashboardQuery: aggregates for all 4 KPI cards
   - BugDensityQuery: issues grouped by FeatureArea (open count, resolved count, avg time to close)
   - TeamPerformanceQuery: tasks completed per user in time window
   - CriticalIssuesQuery: top N open issues ordered by priority + created date
2. Recommendation service: rule-based text generation (e.g., "Feature area X has 3x avg bug density")
3. Export service: CSV builder
4. ReportsController with all API contracts:
   - GET /api/reports/dashboard
   - GET /api/reports/bug-density
   - GET /api/reports/team-performance
   - GET /api/reports/critical-issues
   - POST /api/reports/export?format=csv
5. Authorization: [Authorize] — all users can see reports (no admin-only restriction in SRS)

**Frontend phases after BE**:
6. API service layer: reportsApi.ts + TypeScript types (KpiCardDto, BugDensityDto, TeamPerformanceDto, CriticalIssueDto)
7. ReportsPage shell + ReportsHeader (title, search, refresh button, export button)
8. KpiCardGrid + 4 KpiCard components (value, trend indicator ↑↓, sparkline optional)
9. BugDensityChart (Recharts BarChart grouped by FeatureArea)
10. TeamPerformanceChart (Recharts BarChart or LineChart per user)
11. CriticalIssuesList (ordered list with priority badge)
12. RecommendationPanel (text block from backend rule engine)
13. ExportButton (triggers POST /api/reports/export, downloads file)
14. Refresh flow: RefreshButton invalidates all report queries

Constraints:
- Real-time: polling only (staleTime 5 min) — no SSE/WebSocket
- Export: CSV only (PDF/Excel is future enhancement)
- Recommendations: rule-based text, no ML
- ReportSnapshots table: exists in DB but not used in MVP (on-demand aggregation)

Success criteria:
- All 4 KPI cards display accurate numbers from live data
- Bug density chart renders correctly with FeatureArea grouping
- Team performance chart shows per-user task completion
- CSV export downloads a valid file
- Refresh button triggers data refetch
- Build passes, no TypeScript errors
</planning_requirements>

